            activities={activities} 
            onCreate={handleCreate} 
            onEdit={(a) => { setCurrentActivity(a); setView('editor'); }} 
            onPlay={(a) => { setCurrentActivity(a); setView('player'); }} 
            onDelete={handleDelete}
            onDuplicate={handleDuplicate}
            onExport={handleExport}
            onImport={handleImport}
            onDownloadHTML={handleDownloadHTML}
          />
        )}
        {view === 'help' && <HelpPage />}
        {view === 'editor' && currentActivity && <Editor activity={currentActivity} onSave={handleSave} onPreview={() => setView('player')} />}
        {view === 'player' && currentActivity && <Player activity={currentActivity} onEdit={() => setView('editor')} />}
      </main>
    </div>
  );
}

This happens because Canvas is "helpful" and tries to clean up your code. When you switch back to the "Visual" editor (or sometimes even just by saving in a certain way), Canvas detects that you are linking to a file and automatically rewrites your `<iframe>` tag to use its own standard file viewer (which has the header/sidebar).

**The Solution:**
1.  **Do not switch back to the Visual Editor.** After pasting the code in HTML view `</>`, you must click **Save** immediately.
2.  I have updated the tool to include a **Critical Warning** about this.
3.  I have also fixed the Logic to correctly grab the ID from links like `.../files?preview=12345` (which was failing in your screenshot).
4.  I have significantly increased the **Contrast** of the input fields as requested.

